title: Introduction to swfscDAS
text: addition, can chop effort data segments, summarize conditions sightings segments using das_effort das_effort_sight. effort segments can used line transect estimates using Distance software, species distribution modeling, summarizing number sightings certain species segment, among uses. das_effort chops continuous effort sections (event sequence R E events) effort segments using one several different chopping methods: condition (new effort segment every time condition changes), equal length (effort segments equal length), section (segment full continuous effort section, .e. runs R event E event). das_effort_sight takes output das_effort returns number included sightings animals per segment specified species codes. functions return list three data frames: segdata, sightinfo, randpicks. data frames different chopping methodologies described depth function documentation (?das_effort ?das_effort_sight), briefly segdata contains information effort segment, sightinfo contains information sightings corresponding segment, randpicks contains information specific ‘equal length’ chopping method. das_effort das_effort_sight separate functions allow user control sightings included effort segment summaries (see ?das_effort). See chop/split effort lines strata.
